<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-12389] Upgrade of netty-codec due to CVE-2021-21290</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12389</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Our security tool raised the following security flaw on kafka 2.7: &lt;a href=&quot;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-21290&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-21290&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is a vulnerability related to jar &lt;b&gt;netty-codec-4.1.51.Final.jar&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at source code, the netty-codec in trunk and 2.7.0 branches are still vulnerable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on netty issue tracker, the vulnerability is fixed in 4.1.59.Final: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-5mcr-gq6c-3hq2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-5mcr-gq6c-3hq2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
